g="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/track/6l5OYL8pvH402wTVXjtTYO?go=1&#038;utm_campaign=fAfTD_96_fmly&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=Original&#038;utm_content=d5750c78-f378-4ea3-b783-69fdf7eec43b_none_AD%25C3%2589LA_101983155_MACHINE%2BGIRL_MACHINE%2BGIRL_20250228_direct_capitol-records-us_US_AdELA.lnk.to%2Fmachinegirl&#038;nd=1&#038;dlsi=9466a2e7c9544b56"></iframe></p><p> It comes just days after Grimes (real name Claire Boucher) shared <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-shares-two-new-demos-i-dont-give-a-fuck-im-insane-and-the-fool-listen-3841009">two previously unreleased demos – &#39;I Don&#39;t Give A Fuck, I&#39;m Insane&#39; and &#39;The Fool&#39;</a> .</p><p> Grimes had previously shared the lyrics to the latter on the eve of the 2024 US Presidential election. The track includes the lines: “ <em>Oh you&#39;re a fool/ &#39;Cause you tried to give me the moon/ And all I can give back is poetry</em> ,” an apparent reference to her ex <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/elon-musk">Elon Musk</a> .</p><p> She also recently called out her former partner <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-calls-out-elon-musk-on-x-twitter-for-ignoring-their-childs-medical-crisis-3840013">on social media for allegedly “ignoring” their child&#39;s “medical crisis”</a> . Last week, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-hits-out-at-elon-musk-for-parading-their-son-at-trumps-oval-office-3837427">she criticised Musk for parading their son X around the Oval Office</a> as <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/donald-trump">Trump</a> signed an executive order in front of cameras.</p><p> Grimes, whose latest album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/grimes-miss-anthropocene-review-2612446">&#39;Miss Anthropocene&#39;</a> arrived in 2020, has long been teasing an upcoming two-part record titled <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-update-new-album-book-1-says-music-side-quest-3374707">&#39;Book 1&#39;</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-says-new-album-book-1-is-done-3312001">&#39;Book 2&#39;</a> . She also shared plans to release a prelude EP called <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-to-release-a-prelude-ep-before-the-arrival-of-book-1-3148324">&#39;Fairies Cum First&#39;</a> , and released a single from the project named <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-new-song-shinigami-eyes-3147114">&#39;Shinigami Eyes&#39;</a> in 2022.</p><p> Early last year, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-shares-new-music-teaser-from-the-studio-3576329">Grimes posted a teaser clip of her working in a recording studio</a> . “Sorry I&#39;ve been gone so long,” she said at the time. Excited to get back to work!” In 2023, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-is-making-new-music-i-forgot-this-is-very-fun-3406314">the singer and producer said she was “making music for the first time in ages</a> and I forgot this is very fun”.</p><p> She had previously <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-update-new-album-book-1-says-music-side-quest-3374707">provided an update about the status of &#39;Book 1&#39;</a> , but indicated that music was no longer the main priority in her life by calling it a “side quest”.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/grimes-produces-adelas-new-single-machine-girl-cameos-in-raunchy-video-3842350">Grimes produces ADÉLA&#39;s new single &#39;Machine Girl&#39;, cameos in raunchy video</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
